This directory contains the source for the <screen> library.
Read the top part of the makefile for setting installation parameters.

An early version of <screen> became SysVr3.1 <curses> which begot
many current version of <curses>. This version supports both termcap
and terminfo.  It also provides a number of functions beyond <curses>:
	wmenu:	pop-up/static menus
	wview:	viewing texts in windows
	wunview: dumping a window into a text file in a format suitable
		for nroff/troff or line printers.
	wedit:	editing texts in windows.

The subdirectory Screen_x contains the source for the tput command.

Phong Vo, kpv@research.att.com
